In .NET 10, `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was removed because Android deprecated the underlying `adjustResize` mode. The replacement is the **edge-to-edge** layout model with `AndroidX.Core` window-insets handling.

**Quick fix — use the new `KeyboardResize` API:**

```xml
<!-- Platforms/Android/AndroidManifest.xml -->
<!-- Remove any android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize" -->
```

```csharp
// In your MauiProgram.cs or page handler
#if ANDROID
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(handlers =>
{
    Microsoft.Maui.Handlers.WindowHandler.Mapper.AppendToMapping("KeyboardResize", (handler, view) =>
    {
        var activity = handler.PlatformView as Android.App.Activity;
        activity?.Window?.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(false);

        // Use the new .NET 10 soft input mode
        Microsoft.Maui.ApplicationModel.Platform.CurrentActivity?
            .Window?.SetSoftInputMode(Android.Views.SoftInput.AdjustNothing);
    });
});
#endif
```

**Recommended approach for .NET 10:** Use `CommunityToolkit.Maui` or handle insets manually:

```csharp
// In your chat page (Android platform code or handler)
ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(platformView, (v, insets) =>
{
    var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
    // Adjust bottom padding/margin of your input bar
    v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom);
    return insets;
});
```

**Simplest cross-platform option** — wrap your input in a layout that respects keyboard insets:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ... />
    <Entry Grid.Row="1" x:Name="MessageInput" />
</Grid>
```

Then in your page:

```csharp
#if ANDROID
protected override void OnAppearing()
{
    base.OnAppearing();
    // .NET 10 exposes KeyboardAutoManagerScroll
    KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect(this);
}
#endif
```

**TL;DR:** Replace `adjustResize` with window-insets listeners (`WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()`) or use `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` which is the .NET 10 built-in replacement for automatic keyboard-avoidance behavior.
